The paper deals with the issue of pilot reuse in massive MIMO antenna systems with interfering cells. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses scenarios where the service provider is interested in maximizing the sum rate over a fixed, selected number of users, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY). The use of massive MIMO technology is also a key aspect of the paper, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and communication (cs.COM) systems.
